1. Backend Architecture Overview

✅ Multi-Tenancy Approach:
Option 1: Shared Database + Tenant Filtering (Recommended for MVP)
Option 2: Separate Databases for Each Tenant (For scaling later)

✅ Key Tech Stack:
Backend: Django, DRF
Database: PostgreSQL (Supports multi-tenancy)
Authentication: JWT/OAuth2
Async Tasks: Celery + Redis (For sending invoices & reminders)
Storage: AWS S3 / DigitalOcean Spaces (For invoice PDFs)


✅ Step 1: Set up Django project with DRF
✅ Step 2: Implement Multi-Tenant Authentication
✅ Step 3: Build APIs for Invoice & Expense Management
✅ Step 4: Implement Stripe for SaaS Billing


2. FrontEnd
Now that we've integrated Stripe & PayPal, let's create a customer portal where clients can:
✅ View their invoices
✅ Download PDFs
✅ Pay online (Stripe/PayPal)
✅ See payment history

